{{Orphan|date=March 2013}}
To be included, the outage must conform to these criteria: #The shortage must not be planned by the service provider. #The shortage must affect at least 1,000 people ''and'' last at least one hour. #There must be at least 1,000,000 person*customer hours of disruption.
In other words: * 1,000 people affected for 1,000 hours (42 days) minimum, but if fewer than 1,000 people, event would not be included (regardless of duration) * One million people affected for a minimum of one hour, but if duration is less than one hour, event would not be included (regardless of number of people) * For example, 10,000 people affected for 100 hours ''or'' 100,000 for 10 hours would be included
